<plot>The toys present a musical revue on their own radio station. First, three dolls sing, then a jack-in-the-box doing a 'Bing Crosby' (qv) impression joins in. Then an instrumental piece, with a bead man dancing on a xylophone, a couple of dolls playing matched toy pianos, and various characters dancing on the keyboards. A violinist plays his tune actually, the violin dances around, doing most of the work. A calico dog sings, "I think that I shall never see, a poem lovely as a tree."</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?614926</url></doc>
